THE CHAMPIONSHIPS
June 29, 2019
Alexander Zverev
START_OF_INTERVIEW_TEXT
 
 
  
 
  
  
   
 
THE MODERATOR: Questions, please.   
 Q.  How do you feel basically towards the end of the grass court season?  At what point do you think your game is at on grass?  
ALEXANDER ZVEREV: Yeah, it's good.  We're at Wimbledon, so it better has to be good.   
Yeah, I mean, it's always a short grass court season.  I hope I can have it for two more weeks.  We'll see how it goes.  But I feel well.  I've been practicing well.  We'll see how it goes well.   
 Q.  With the big three keeping on going, do you think we're near to a changing of the guard with tennis?  
ALEXANDER ZVEREV: Yeah, I think they're going to be around for a while.  It's for us to decide whether we're going to compete with them or whether we're going to actually beat them at some point during the big tournaments.   
Nobody of us has done yet.  I've beaten a few guys obviously in Masters Series and at the World Tour Finals.  If we talk about Grand Slams, they still win pretty much everything.  It's for one of us young guys to take that away a little bit.  Maybe this will be the tournament.  Who knows.   
  
  
  
  
  

END_OF_INTERVIEW_TEXT